msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/navigating/3d_view.rst:256
msgid "If You Get Lost"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/navigating/3d_view.rst:258
msgid ""
"If you get lost in 3D space, which is not uncommon, two hotkeys will help "
"you: :kbd:`home` changes the view so that you can see all objects "
"(:menuselection:`View --> View All` menu entry), while :kbd:`pad.` zooms the"
" view to the currently selected objects when in perspective mode "
"(:menuselection:`View --> View Selected` menu entry)."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/navigating/3d_view.rst:266
msgid "Zoom Border"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/navigating/3d_view.rst:268
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Zoom Border` tool allows you to specify a rectangular region "
"and zoom in so that the region fills the 3d view."
